'''書湯'''（{{lang-en|'''Book Soup'''}}）是一家位於[[美國|美國]][[洛杉磯|洛杉磯]]的[[獨立書店|獨立書店]]，位於[[西好萊塢|西好萊塢]]的[[日落大道|日落大道]]上。這家店以其高聳、堆滿書本並且排列複雜的書架而知名，吸引了許多到訪的遊客。<ref name="Obit">{{cite web |author=By louis sahagun January 4, 2009 |url=http://www.latimes.com/news/obituaries/la-me-goldman4-2009jan04,0,2106470.story |title=Sahagun, Louis. "Glenn Goldman, Owner of Book Soup, Dies at 58." ''Los Angeles Times.'' January 4, 2009 |publisher=Latimes.com |date=2009-01-04 |accessdate=2013-12-04 |archive-date=2012-10-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121026120556/http://www.latimes.com/news/obituaries/la-me-goldman4-2009jan04,0,2106470.story |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="George">{{cite web |url=http://articles.latimes.com/2000/sep/15/news/cl-21283 |title=George, Lynell. "Poets, Transvestites and a Pile of Books." ''Los Angeles Times.'' September 15, 2000 |publisher=Articles.latimes.com |date=2000-09-15 |accessdate=2013-12-04 |archive-date=2015-01-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150106080912/http://articles.latimes.com/2000/sep/15/news/cl-21283 |dead-url=no }}</ref> 這家書店在娛樂產業界廣受歡迎，主持了許多知名作家的活動，包括[[穆罕默德·阿里|穆罕默德·阿里]]、{{le|霍華德·斯特恩|Howard Stern}}、[[安妮·萊柏維茲|安妮·萊柏維茲]]、[[恰克·帕拉尼克|恰克·帕拉尼克]]、[[珍娜·詹姆森|珍娜·詹姆森]]、[[門戶樂團|門戶樂團]]等。<ref name="Cornell">{{cite web |url=http://www.publishersweekly.com/article/CA6561941.html |title=Werris, Wendy. "Tyson Cornell Helps Keep Things Hot for Book Soup." ''Publishers Weekly.'' May 19, 2008 |publisher=Publishersweekly.com |date= |accessdate=2013-12-04 |archive-date=2015-01-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150106080232/http://www.publishersweekly.com/article/CA6561941.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="Alimurung">[http://www.laweekly.com/2007-05-17/art-books/the-host-and-his-prot-g-e/ Alimurung, Gendy. "The Host and His Protégée."] {{Wayback|url=http://www.laweekly.com/2007-05-17/art-books/the-host-and-his-prot-g-e/ |date=20150106080414 }} ''LA Weekly.'' May 16, 2007.</ref> 另外，作為日落大道上的文化樞紐，書湯時常被用作電影、電視劇的場景。<ref name="George" />

1975年格倫·戈德曼所創立了這家店。<ref name="Cornell" /><ref name="Latham">{{cite web|author=AARON LATHAMPublished: August 02, 1992 |url=http://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=9E0CE3DF1730F931A3575BC0A964958260&sec=travel&spon=&pagewanted=2 |title=Latham, Aaron. "L.A.: A Script for Book Buying." ''New York Times.'' August 2, 1992 |publisher=New York Times |date=1992-08-02 |accessdate=2013-12-04}}</ref>

